cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.MM

This paper presents a data-driven method based on a U-Net architecture that approximates the non-linear relation between a contact force and the displacement field computed by a FEM algorithm. The method uses deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the computational cost of the finite element method and presents ideas to reduce computation times, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of deep learning to enhance computational mechanics is a topic that can be classified under both machine learning (cs.LG) and computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper presents benchmark examples of various geometries and topologies, which can be considered as a computer graphics and computer vision problem (cs.MM).
